{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b9e4c481-40cd-4e30-b834-138682eaa685","content":"Here's the correct skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute | Example |\n|-----------|-----------|---------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore]` | `[Ignore(\"Bug #123 - pending fix\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `Skip` property | `[Fact(Skip = \"Bug #123\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"Bug #123\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore]` | `[Ignore(\"Bug #123 - pending fix\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip]` | `[Skip(\"Bug #123 - pending fix\")]` |\n\n**Key differences:**\n- **xUnit** is unique — skip is a *property* on `[Fact]`/`[Theory]`, not a separate attribute.\n- **MSTest**, **NUnit**, and **TUnit** use standalone attributes with the reason as a constructor argument.\n- All four frameworks will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in results, with your reason message visible in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0d769e29-9387-4361-916d-ee92b2fbe779","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a straightforward knowledge question - I don't need to invoke any skills or tools for this.\n\nHere are the correct attributes:\n\n**MSTest**: `[Ignore(\"reason\")]`\n**xUnit**: `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]`\n**NUnit**: `[Ignore(\"reason\")]`\n**TUnit**: `[Skip(\"reason\")]`","outputTokens":396,"requestId":"D000:91905:14D424C:18189BF:69EC136D"},"id":"f4c4c94c-6659-4293-9184-324da782956f","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:05:57.371Z","parentId":"7dedecbd-63c0-4fb8-80e3-1e4f94515cfc"}
